column1: Contains the date from CalLite-CV, the CalSim date, and various CalSim II records' values after that. These can be combined using the equations in diversionoverview.csv; here's an example. Upper Sac is represented as D104/C109 in cell B2 of diversionoverview.csv, so for 10/2014 that's equal to 262.37/6145=0.043. Some calculations have multipliers and one even subtracts one of the arcs instead of summing them all; all that math is from the Proposed Mapping by Mike Urkov a year or two ago.
